OS_ConvertSpacedCardinal4  (&E4)
#Parent OS_Convert
=>	R0 =	value to be converted
	R1 =	pointer to buffer for resulting string
	R2 =	size of buffer

<=	R0 =	pointer to buffer (R1 on entry)
	R1 =	pointer to terminator
	R2 =	free bytes in buffer

This SWI converts a value into an unsigned string of decimal characters with space separators every thousand. The number can be 0 to 4 294 967 295 (13 characters).
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 469=>PRM-1:469>.
